      <akn:section eId="sec_28:2A_212">
        <akn:num>28:2A-212</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Implied warranty of merchantability.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2A-212_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Except in a finance lease, a warranty that the goods will be merchantable is implied in a lease contract if the lessor is a merchant with respect to goods of that kind.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2A-212_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Goods to be merchantable must:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2A-212_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Other implied warranties may arise from course of dealing or usage of trade.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
